            <span style="font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-muted);">July 15, 2026</span>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 8px;">
            Security Patch &amp; Stability Release — Critical vulnerability fixes across File Manager, installation script, and graceful shutdown.
          </p>
          <ul style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); padding-left: 16px; margin: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px;">
            <li><strong>[CRIT-1]</strong> Shell injection fix — replaced shell interpolation with <code>execFile()</code>.</li>
            <li><strong>[CRIT-2]</strong> Zip Slip protection in File Manager.</li>
            <li><strong>[CRIT-3]</strong> Upload extension filter (18 dangerous types).</li>
            <li><strong>[HIGH-1]</strong> Graceful shutdown race condition fix (WAL-safe).</li>
            <li><strong>[HIGH-4]</strong> Install dir fix (<code>/opt/linux-panel</code> → <code>/opt/panelku</code>).</li>
            <li><strong>[MED-7]</strong> Storage permission hardened to <code>750</code>.</li>
            <li><strong>install.sh:</strong> Multi-distro rewrite with secure secrets.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

